review_blob: A fairly decent beer with clean crisp traditional lager flavor, lacks the boldness to seperate it from all the other lagers
A very, very dark, almost black colored stout.  It has a unique taste that can be appreciated if you like a heavy beer, otherwise, avoid it if you are primarily a lager, light beer drinker
Gilden, while one of the oldest Kolschs, does not have the fresh crisp taste that it should.
This beer is incredible, I actually had it in Cologne, It is a great lighter flavored beer
